ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was a really great intro class that exposes to you important topics in bioinformatics. For an MBB or BBSB student, the beginning class was a lot of review, but it developed into a lot of new topics.
I would not recommend this course. I do not feel that I learned much in the way of content nor did I obtain any mastery of new skills to carry on into other courses or work that I will be doing.
no you dont learn much but just get exposed to things. i could summurize everything i learned in this course in 1 hour

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: My thesis will be heavy in bioinformatics and next generation sequencing analysis, so the course was very relevant!!
